  "text": "to images containing horizontal and vertical lines in novel locations. Figures 7A and 7B show the feature representations inferred by the tIBP and IBP, respectively, when given 100 images composed of a vertical bar and a horizontal bar each occurring in the image with probability .8 in a position drawn uniformly at random over the image. Not surprisingly (since the IBP assumes features occur identically in every image), the IBP model infers a feature for different positions of the lines (similar to the solution of [CITATION_1] and some of the objects themselves. The tIBP model infers a horizontal bar and a vertical bar that occur in different positions-a better solution.",
